-- Real Madrid to Offer Benzema for Wayne Rooney, Sun Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2010-10-18T10:45:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/real-madrid-plans-battle-to-sign-united-s-wayne-rooney-star-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Benzema for Rooney?  Real Madrid will offer France national team player  Karim Benzema  plus cash for Manchester United striker  Wayne Rooney ,
 the Sun said .  The transaction would be worth about 50 million pounds
($79.5 million), the newspaper said. Real manager  Jose Mourinho 
and President  Florentino Perez  want to sign Rooney, who’s
unsettled because of media reports about his personal life, the
newspaper said.  Carroll Charged  England Under-21 and Newcastle striker  Andy Carroll  was
charged with assault,  the Daily Mail said.   The 21-year-old is scheduled to appear at Tynedale
Magistrates Court in Northumberland this morning, the newspaper
said.  Tuncay Away?  Stoke striker Tuncay left the Reebok Stadium after being
left out of the team’s 18-man squad this weekend,  the Sun said.   The 28-year-old Turk, who left in a taxi before kickoff,
said last week he wants to leave the club after getting into
just two league games as a substitute, the newspaper said.  Chelsea Youth  Chelsea will turn to reserve team players for the Champions
League match at Spartak Moscow tomorrow because of injuries to
first-team players,  the Mail said .  Forward Gael Kakuta, 19, and midfielder Josh McEachran, 17,
may get to play after  Didier Drogba  and  Frank Lampard  missed the
0-0 draw with Aston Villa at the weekend, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
